						               													<description>An entertaining dice game about addition and substraction in a number range between +20 and -20 for 2 to 4 players from age 8.&amp;#10;Each player selects 2 cards and puts them down before him. Each card shows 5 fields with dice printed in them. Some fields offer chances to gain points, others are traps and have to be avoided. Players score by being fast in putting down a line of 10 dice in 10 different colurs by placing them cleverly under theeir two cards.&amp;#10;To start the game, the 66 coloured dice are cast. Then the players play simultaneously. Each player grabs 10 dice one by one and forms his line of 10 dice in 10 different colours. As speed is a decisive factor players tend to make mistakes when arranging their dice and get trapped by the trap fields. This, of course, is part of the fun and motivates to do less mistakes in the next playthrough.&amp;#10;There are 2 versions of the game: an easier one with two levels for players from age 8 ++, which is called &amp;quot;Farbenspiel&amp;quot;, and a version and an even more challenging version with 4 levels for players from age 12 ++ (called &amp;quot;Etappenspiel&amp;quot;).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
